data.chText: 延长；扩大；扩展
data.enText: make longer/larger/wider

data.chText: 使伸长；扩大；扩展
data.enText: to make sth longer or larger

data.chText: 扩建护栏 / 公路 / 房子
data.enText: to extend a fence/road/house

data.chText: 现已有扩大无烟区的计划。
data.enText: There are plans to extend the no-smoking area.

data.chText: 延长；使延期
data.enText: to make sth last longer

data.chText: 延长最后期限 / 签证
data.enText: to extend a deadline/visa

data.chText: 展览会又延长了六周。
data.enText: The show has been extended for another six weeks.

data.chText: 精心保养可延长汽车寿命。
data.enText: Careful maintenance can extend the life of your car.

data.chText: 扩大…的范围（或影响）
data.enText: to make a business, an idea, an influence, etc. cover more areas or operate in more places

data.chText: 公司打算将业务扩展到欧洲。
data.enText: The company plans to extend its operations into Europe.

data.chText: 学校正在拓宽授课学科的范围。
data.enText: The school is extending the range of subjects taught.

data.chText: 包括
data.enText: include

data.chText: 适用于；包括
data.enText: to relate to or include sb/sth

data.chText: 这项优惠不包括雇员的伴侣。
data.enText: The offer does not extend to employees' partners.

data.chText: 他的乐意帮助只不过限于打几个电话罢了。
data.enText: His willingness to help did not extend beyond making a few phone calls.

data.chText: 涉及范围 / 时间 / 距离
data.enText: cover area/time/distance

data.chText: 涉及（范围）；延伸（距离）；延续（时间）
data.enText: to cover a particular area, distance or length of time

data.chText: 我们的土地一直延伸到河边。
data.enText: Our land extends as far as the river.

data.chText: 他的写作生涯超过了40年。
data.enText: His writing career extended over a period of 40 years.

data.chText: 使达到；使延伸
data.enText: to make sth reach sth or stretch

data.chText: 在两根柱子间拉根绳子
data.enText: to extend a rope between two posts

data.chText: 身体部位
data.enText: part of body

data.chText: 伸展，舒展，展开（尤指手臂或腿）
data.enText: to stretch part of your body, especially an arm or a leg, away from yourself

data.chText: 他伸出手来与新雇员握手。
data.enText: He extended his hand to (= offered to shake hands with) the new employee.

data.chText: 向另一个国家伸出友谊之手
data.enText: to extend the hand of friendship to (= try to have good relations with) another country

data.chText: 提供；给予
data.enText: offer/give

data.chText: 提供；给予
data.enText: to offer or give sth to sb

data.chText: 我肯定你们会同我一起向我们的客人表示热烈的欢迎。
data.enText: I'm sure you will join me in extending a very warm welcome to our visitors.

data.chText: 殷勤款待外国留学生
data.enText: to extend hospitality to overseas students

data.chText: 发出邀请
data.enText: to extend an invitation

data.chText: 银行拒绝向他们提供信贷。
data.enText: The bank refused to extend credit to them (= to lend them money) .

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.chText: 努力；尽力
data.enText: use effort/ability

data.chText: 使竭尽全力
data.enText: to make sb/sth use all their effort, abilities, supplies, etc.

data.chText: 吉姆大可不必为这次考试那么拼命。
data.enText: Jim didn't really have to extend himself in the exam.

data.chText: 这场流行病已使各医院以最大负荷运转。
data.enText: Hospitals were already fully extended because of the epidemic.

simple_means.memory_skill: ex 出 + tend 伸展 → 伸出去 → 扩张

means: 伸展，舒展，展开（尤指手臂或腿）

ex.enText: Our summer vacation extended into September.
He wanted to extend his garden.

ex.chText: 我的农场一直延伸到河边。
ex.enText: My farm extends as far as the river.

synonyms.bx: 多指在空间、时间、面积等方面延长或扩展。

ex.chText: 随着冬天的来临，夜晚渐渐变长了。
ex.enText: Nights are lengthening with the coming of winter.

ex.chText: 节省时间就是延长生命。
ex.enText: To save time is to lengthen life.

synonyms.bx: 指在长度或时间上拉长或延长。

ex.chText: 他尽一切努力来延长母亲的生命。
ex.enText: He tried hard to prolong his mother's life.
The treaty has been prolonged for another 5 years.

synonyms.bx: 通常指时间上的延长，含超过正常限度之意。

tr: extend one's limbs or muscles, or the entire body
example: Stretch your legs!
Extend your right arm above your head

tr: thrust or extend out
example: He held out his hand
point a finger
extend a hand
the bee exserted its sting

tr: increase in quantity or bulk by adding a cheaper substance
example: stretch the soup by adding some more cream
extend the casserole with a little rice

tr: continue or extend
example: The civil war carried into the neighboring province
The disease extended into the remote mountain provinces

tr: lengthen in time
cause to be or last longer
example: We prolonged our stay
She extended her visit by another day
The meeting was drawn out until midnight

tr: prolong the time allowed for payment of
example: extend the loan

tr: extend in scope or range or area
example: The law was extended to all citizens
widen the range of applications
broaden your horizon
Extend your backyard

tr: expand the influence of
example: The King extended his rule to the Eastern part of the continent

tr: use to the utmost
exert vigorously or to full capacity
example: He really extended himself when he climbed Kilimanjaro
Don't strain your mind too much

tr: open or straighten out
unbend
example: Can we extend the legs of this dining table?

tr: cause to move at full gallop
example: Did you gallop the horse just now?

tr: extend or stretch out to a greater or the full length
example: Unfold the newspaper
stretch out that piece of cloth
extend the TV antenna

tr: offer verbally
example: extend my greetings
He offered his sympathy

tr: make available
provide
example: extend a loan
The bank offers a good deal on new mortgages

tr: stretch out over a distance, space, time, or scope
run or extend between two points or beyond a certain point
example: Service runs all the way to Cranbury
His knowledge doesn't go very far
My memory extends back to my fourth year of life
The facts extend beyond a consideration of her personal assets

tr: span an interval of distance, space or time
example: The war extended over five years
The period covered the turn of the century
My land extends over the hills on the horizon
This farm covers some 200 acres
The Archipelago continues for another 500 miles

tr: reach outward in space
example: The awning extends several feet over the sidewalk

value.def: If you say that something, usually something large, extends for a particular distance or extends from one place to another, you are indicating its size or position.

example.ex: The caves extend for some 18 kilometres...
example.tran: 那些洞穴深约18公里。

example.ex: The main stem will extend to around 12ft, if left to develop naturally...
example.tran: 如果任其自然生长，主干可以长到约12英尺。

example.ex: Our personal space extends about 12 to 18 inches around us...
example.tran: 我们的个人空间是周围12到18英寸的范围。

example.ex: The high-speed train service is planned to extend from Paris to Bordeaux...
example.tran: 高铁拟从巴黎延伸至波尔多。

example.ex: The new territory would extend over one-fifth of Canada's land mass.
example.tran: 这块新领土将会使加拿大陆地面积扩展1/5以上。

value.def: If an object extends from a surface or place, it sticks out from it.

example.ex: A shelf of land extended from the escarpment.
example.tran: 悬崖上凸出一块空地。

value.def: If an event or activity extends over a period of time, it continues for that time.

example.ex: ...a playing career in first-class cricket that extended from 1894 to 1920...
example.tran: 从1894年延续至1920年的板球甲级比赛职业生涯

example.ex: The courses are based on a weekly two-hour class, extending over a period of 25 weeks.
example.tran: 这些课程每周上一节课，每节两个小时，持续25周。

value.def: If something extends to a group of people, things, or activities, it includes or affects them.

example.ex: The service also extends to wrapping and delivering gifts...
example.tran: 服务项目还包括包装和递送礼物。

example.ex: The talks will extend to the church, human rights groups and other social organizations...
example.tran: 会谈将涉及教会、人权团体和其他社会组织。

example.ex: His influence extends beyond the TV viewing audience.
example.tran: 他的影响扩展到电视观众之外。

value.def: If you extend something, you make it longer or bigger.

example.ex: This year they have introduced three new products to extend their range...
example.tran: 今年他们发布了3种新产品，以扩大产品范围。

example.ex: The building was extended in 1500.
example.tran: 那座建筑于1500年扩建。

example.ex: ...an extended exhaust pipe.
example.tran: 加长的排气管

value.def: If a piece of equipment or furniture extends, its length can be increased.

example.ex: ... a table which extends to accommodate extra guests...
example.tran: 展开后可坐更多客人的桌子

example.ex: The table extends to 220cm.
example.tran: 桌子伸展后长220厘米。

value.def: If you extend something, you make it last longer than before or end at a later date.

example.ex: They have extended the deadline by twenty-four hours.
example.tran: 他们已经将最后期限延长了24小时。

example.ex: ...an extended contract.
example.tran: 延期的合同

value.def: If you extend something to other people or things, you make it include or affect more people or things.

example.ex: It might be possible to extend the technique to other crop plants.
example.tran: 也许可以将这种技术应用于其他农作物。

value.def: If someone extends their hand, they stretch out their arm and hand to shake hands with someone.

example.ex: The man extended his hand: 'I'm Chuck'.
example.tran: 那名男子伸出手说道：“我是查克。”
